"help.basics.title" = "Understanding Logic Gates";
"help.basics.content" = "Logic gates are the building blocks of digital circuits. Each gate takes one or more inputs and produces an output based on a specific logical operation.\n\nDigital signals can be either 0 (false/low) or 1 (true/high). In Bools:\n• Green light = 1 (true)\n• Grey/dim = 0 (false)\n\nGates process these signals according to their logic rules.";

"help.interface.title" = "User Interface";
"help.interface.content" = "The interface consists of three main areas:\n\n• Toolbar: Quick access buttons for common operations\n• Sidebar: Gate palette for dragging gates onto the canvas\n• Canvas: Main work area where you design circuits\n• Inspector: Shows properties of selected gates\n\nYou can toggle the sidebar and inspector with keyboard shortcuts ⌘1 and ⌘2.";

"help.logicGates.title" = "Logic Gates Reference";
"help.logicGates.content" = "Bools includes 16 different logic gate types:\n\nBasic Gates: AND, OR, NOT\nAdvanced: XOR, NAND, NOR, XNOR\nSpecial: Implication gates, projection gates\nInput/Output: INPUT and OUTPUT gates for setting and reading signals\nConstants: Always 0 or Always 1\n\nEach gate has a specific truth table that defines its behavior.";

"help.physicalComponents.title" = "Physical Components";
"help.physicalComponents.content" = "Beyond pure logic gates, Bools includes realistic physical components:\n\n• Button: Momentary switch - active only when pressed\n• Switch: Toggle switch - maintains state until flipped\n• LED: Light-emitting diode - glows green when active\n• Bulb: Incandescent light - glows yellow when powered\n• Relay: Electromagnetic switch with COM, NO, NC contacts\n• Buzzer: Emits sound when activated\n• Battery: Power source\n• Resistor & Capacitor: Passive components\n\nThese components let you design practical circuits.";

"help.transistors.title" = "Transistors";
"help.transistors.content" = "Transistors are active components that can amplify or switch signals:\n\n• BJT (Bipolar Junction Transistor):\n  - NPN: Conducts when base is high\n  - PNP: Conducts when base is low\n\n• MOSFET (Metal-Oxide-Semiconductor):\n  - N-channel: Conducts when gate is high\n  - P-channel: Conducts when gate is low\n\nTransistors are commonly used in amplifier circuits and logic circuit implementations.";

"help.circuits.title" = "Building Circuits";
"help.circuits.content" = "To create a circuit:\n\n1. Add gates from the sidebar\n2. Arrange them logically on the canvas\n3. Connect outputs to inputs with wires\n4. Set input values to test\n5. Observe the signal flow\n\nTips:\n• Use INPUT gates to manually set test values\n• Use OUTPUT gates to display results\n• Organize gates left-to-right for clarity\n• Group related gates together\n• Use the inspector to rename gates for documentation";

"help.simulation.title" = "Real-time Simulation";
"help.simulation.content" = "Bools simulates your circuit in real-time as you modify it.\n\nThe simulation engine:\n• Calculates all gate outputs based on inputs\n• Handles complex circuits with loops\n• Updates instantly when you change inputs\n• Shows signal values on connecting wires\n• Detects and handles circular dependencies\n\nWatch the green and grey indicator lights to see signal flow through your circuit.";

"help.examples.title" = "Learning Examples";
"help.examples.content" = "Bools includes example circuits to help you learn:\n\n• Half Adder: Add two binary numbers\n• Full Adder: Three-bit addition\n• SR Latch: Basic memory circuit\n• D Flip-Flop: Synchronized memory\n• Ring Oscillator: Self-oscillating circuit\n• Relay circuits: Physical component examples\n• Traffic Light Controller: Multi-output logic\n\nLoad examples from the toolbar or try building your own variations!";

